items.name: Nu Element
items.description:
✦ Nu Element

💚 for Updates - I would love to see your reviews and images of this model, feel free to post them below!

This model keeps surprising me and currently reigns as one of my favorites generally speaking as well as among my unreleased/released models. I made this mix one day after experimenting with some other merges using MBW. I essentially started with an uncommon base and used some common to uncommon weight presets testing by eye merging in aspects of models as I went.

The final result really brings together some of the styling I enjoy in a neutral fashion. Some great detail, great texture and lighting/reflections, semi-soft/muted tones, and an overall mostly-stable creative flexibility with prompts and configurations across the board. Hopefully you enjoy this one as much as I have ~ feel free to let me know!

💡 Alternate versions and more information can be found on the Hugging Face page.

General Use

I've found this model to be decently flexible - use the parameters you find best.
The preview image and gallery sections can give you a good base as a starting point. Start simple, then go from there.

Be keen of any conflicting styles and how tokens may 'lean' the model toward one style or another. Some prompts may be a bit messy, but overall should be able to be toned down or reworked. For a soft/neutral anime style, keep prompts from being too heavy on realistic style tokens. You can enhance an anime style (or others) with related terms such as anime, 2d, flat color, outlines, etc.

~20 steps, 7 scale, ~0.4 denoising, clip skip 1 or 2, is a good starting point

Tips

This model currently loses a bit of clarity/detail with eyes at a mid-far to far character distance depending. This can be remedied at times by either changing your prompt to exclude certain tokens such as full body and/or upscaling the image once again using the img2img upscaler. Hires fix upscale initially is already assumed to be used.

Hands/fingers are generally passable. Try to tweak your parameters/prompt if you're having issues. This model is powerful, but not perfect. A high hires fix denoising value, your upscaler choice, etc. may cause some issues at times. You can also take a look at various negative embeddings to mitigate any issues.

Samplers

I've found a lot of samplers work great being fairly similar across the board with this version. Have fun and try some common and uncommon configurations.

VAE

Use whichever VAE you find best. Included is a renamed vae-ft-ema-560000-ema vae (SuperMixA.vae). Models containing a baked-in VAE, found on the Hugging Face page, are listed as -bv or -bakedVAE making the use of a VAE file redundant.

vae-ft-mse-840000-ema and ClearVAE_V2.3 can also be good options.

Keeping things simple for now. I might add to this page including some simple prompt presets or so if I decide to update or add anything.

Note: this version/model is not finetuned to maximum detail accuracy.

Disclaimer

This model(s) may output NSFW content unintentionally depending on parameters used. Make sure you tailor your prompts accordingly. For example "nsfw" in the negative prompt.

The purpose of sharing this model is not to showcase obscene material in a public forum. The use of this learning model is entirely at the discretion of the user, and they have the freedom to choose whether or not to create SFW or NSFW content. The decision of whether to engage with SFW or NSFW content lies with the user and their own personal preferences. The ai model(s) do not contain explicit visual content that can be accessed easily.

Example Images used

  • vae-ft-ema-560000-ema vae

  • 4x-UltraSharp or R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B upscalers

  • hires fix w/ some upscaled again using SD upscale

  • use old karras scheduler signmas (0.1 to 10) compatibility setting

  • any LoRa use should be listed in the image metadata

  • Bad_v2 negative embedding renamed should be the same as bad_prompt_version2

  • EasyNegative and badhandv4 negative embeddings were also used

*Negative embeddings are optional

Resources

This model merge (v1) used the following resources - all of these are great stand-alone, props to each creator.

  • FeelYou_a2 (removed, iirc was via Bradcatt)

  • Counterfeit_v3 (via rqdwdw)

  • Pika's New Generation_v2 (via PikaDesigner)

  • SuperMix (via myself)

  • Dark Sushi Mix-Darker (via Aitasai)

  • GyozaMix_v3 (has a lot of great aspects, especially in mixes!, via Jemnite)

  • Rev Animated_v1.2.2 (via s6yx)

items.name: Monica Huldt (Swedish Bella)
items.description:
A request of @augdiana.

Monica Huldt, aka Swedish Bella, is (contrarily to what her nickname would indicate) a Polish social media celebrity and Onlyfans model with around 2.5M followers on Instagram.

This is a 130-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings. It's also one of the fastest I've ever trained. ^^

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (swbella:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Minigirl
items.description:
After specializing in miniaturized person-related content, I wanted to share some tips for using LoRA models specifically for minigirls. If you're interested in creating artwork or designs featuring miniaturized people the size of pencils, I recommend using the Midnight Mixer Melt as the base model. This model works well when fine-tuned with minigirl-related embeddings.

For optimal results, you can use embeddings for minigirl characters such as Lily, Mia, or Tiny Tina. However, the model can also generate images of minigirls without specific embeddings.

To enhance the vibrancy of colors, I suggest using the WD VAE. Additionally, it's important to set the CLIP skip to 2 to ensure smooth generation.

Weight recommendations for the LoRA model:

  • For v2_offset: between 1 and 0.6 (Only available if you are a minigirl)

  • For v2_original: between 0.5 and 0.3 (Only available if you possess the ancient minigirl language)

  • For v1: around 0.8

When using this model, make sure to include the trigger keyword "minigirlstyle" to generate minigirl-specific results. You can also try using keywords like "Lily" or "tiny person" to further refine the generated content.

Please note that LoRA is intended to be used within the context of minigirl-related content. It is not a standalone model, and it is not designed for general image generation.

To use LoRA in the auto1111 framework, follow these steps:

  1. Update the webui by using the "git pull" command or redownload it.

  2. Copy the LoRA file to the "stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora" directory.

  3. Select the LoRA model within the web interface, as shown in the accompanying video.

  4. If necessary, adjust the weight settings for optimal results. By default, the weight is set to 1.

While it may be possible to mix this approach with a Wano style embedding, I have not personally tested it, and it is unlikely to be necessary. Overall, this LoRA model produces cleaner results with fewer background artifacts or irregularities.

Enjoy exploring the world of minigirls with LoRA and unleash your creativity!

This model will turn any humanoid subject into a furry and will even turn animal prompts into furries (sometimes), but it works best if you put the type of animal and add furry to the prompt like "alligator furry," or "horse furry." If you type in dragon, you may get a dragon or you may get a dragonoid furry. To make sure it is a furry, put in "dragon furry" instead.

Some of the animals I've tried, like cow, horse, snake, bird, didn't turn into furries well, probably because there wasn't the best sample set in the model. However, you should be able to turn them into furries by increasing the prompt strength and doing some prompt engineering.

The model has Blessed2 VAE baked into it, so no VAE required.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.

Example promts; talojipanam with jacket standing in a badland like area / talojipanam without jacket standing in a room.

Dataset for the model was around 38 pictures including pictures from the web and in game and manually captioning images.

自今年2月开始，生成式人工智能工具如雨后春笋一般涌出。

我自己也伴随着它们的发展，从ChatGPT到midjourney再到stable diffusion。科技树一路点过来。

人们总问宇宙的尽头是什么？复合这个时代的回答是：宇宙的尽头是带货。

有了AI 工具，带货更就更简单了，我不禁在思考，如果大家都在带货，那谁生产呢。除了带货，AI 可以更好的服务生活嘛，服务我们 “人”本身。

千言万语，AI 除了用来带货，还可以用来做哪些有意义的事？

这是我的思考。

————

于是乎，在我学习了lora模型店训练，我开始着手了这个京剧脸谱的训练工作。

这只是我的思考与初次训练尝试，模型会有很多缺点，与问题。

诚挚的欢迎大家返图，以及提供宝贵建议与意见。

我们一起探索AI工具如何更好服务我们的文明。

没有人的文明将毫无意义。

这里是ZX_zuobian

————————————

Generative AI tools have been springing up since February of this year.

I myself have accompanied their development, from ChatGPT to midjourney to stable diffusion. the tech tree points all the way through.

People always ask what's at the end of the universe? Compounding this era the answer is: the end of the universe is bandwagon.

With AI tools, banding is even easier. I can't help but think, if everyone is banding, who is producing. In addition to bringing goods, AI can better serve life, service our "people" itself.

In a thousand words, AI can be used to do what meaningful things in addition to bringing goods?

This is my thinking.

----

So, after I learned the lora model store training, I began to work on the training of this Beijing opera face.

This is just my thinking & first training attempt, the model will have many drawbacks, & problems.

Sincerely welcome you to return the picture, as well as provide valuable suggestions and comments.

Together we can explore how AI tools can better serve our civilization.

Civilization would be meaningless without people.
